<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197487>
    dc:description "FIGURES 28 – 33. Microcerella asymmetrica sp. nov. 28. Male holotype, left lateral view. 29. Cerci, dorsal (or posterior) view. 30. Left cercus, lateral view. 31. Pregonite and postgonite, left lateral view. 32. Phallus, left lateral view. 33. Phallus, apical (or ventral) view. Scale bars = 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: albj, anterior lobe of juxta; h (lp), harpes (or lateral plates); j, juxta; lbj, lobes of juxta; llbj, lateral lobe of juxta; lst, lateral styli; po, postgonite; pr, pregonite; sur, surstylus; v, vesica." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/197487/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

